claimants and defendants and </span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:11pt">would like to see further details on this measure</span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:11pt"> before </span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:11pt">a swift implementation process in </span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:11pt">spring</span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:11pt"> 2014.</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">4. Small Claims Track Threshold</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:11pt">The current limit of £1,000 for personal injury claims means that a large proportion of RTA PI claims are going through the courts, which leaves defendants facing </span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:11pt">significantly higher costs and litigation for personal injury claims brought against them.</span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:11pt">Enterprise believes that </span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:11pt">raising the threshold for small claims to £5,</span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:11pt">000 would ensure defendants are not saddled with extensive legal costs and litigation for cl</span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:11pt">aim</span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:11pt">s of a relatively low value.</span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:11pt">It would also help reduce the cost of whiplash claims</span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:11pt"> overall</span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:11pt"> by </span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:11pt">ending the requirement</span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:11pt"> for costly legal advice in many </span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:11pt">claims above £1,000.</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:11pt">We also believe that increasing the small claims track is</span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:11pt"> fundamental to </span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:11pt">ensuring </span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:11pt">fraudulent and exaggerated whiplash claims are challenged</span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:11pt">. By ensuring a far greater number of claims proceed through </span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:11pt">the small claims track</span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:11pt">, the cost of challenging such claims significantly diminishes. </span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:11pt">In the past, the cost of challenging </span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:11pt">potentially </span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:11pt">fra</span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:11pt">udulent or</span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:11pt"> exaggerated claims has caused insurers to consistently make pre-medical report offers to claimants to offset potential litigation costs of challenging a claim outside the small claims track.</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:11pt">This issue has been longstanding and we would highlight that in 2005-06, the Citizens Advice Bureau, in written evidence to the Constitutional Affairs Committee inquiry into </span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">The Courts: small claims</span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:11pt">, suggested that with proper regulation there was a “stron</span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:11pt">g argument” that more cases could be dealt under the small claims track, possibly by raising the threshold for personal injury cases to £5,000. The Bureau also said that is supported the principle behind a wide small claims jurisdiction to ensure consumer </span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:11pt">friendliness and end the requirement to hire expensive legal professionals.</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:11pt">We accept that there are concerns, especially from stakeholders in the personal injury sector, that genuine claimants could be inhibited in </span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:11pt">their access to justice and entitlement</span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:11pt"> t</span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:11pt">o full compensatory amounts</span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:11pt">, however </span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:11pt">we </span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:11pt">believe</span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:11pt"> that a number of approaches</span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:11pt">,</span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:11pt"> which would offset these concerns,</span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:11pt">could be </span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:11pt">taken if a decision was made to introduce</span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:11pt"> a higher small claims threshold. </span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:11pt">We agree with the Transport Select Committee that the Go</span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:11pt">vernment should provide analysis on ways in which the small claims track could be combined with routine submission of expert evidence. We believe that if</span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:11pt"> the threshold rise was accompanied by</span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:11pt"> measures to make medical reports mandatory for all personal inju</span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:11pt">ry claims, this would ensure that all cases have received an expert assessment, regardless of the claims track used</span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:11pt">.</span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:11pt"> We would also suggest that the introduction of independent and impartial medical boards will provide a rigorous assessment of all claims, wh</span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:11pt">ich would alleviate c</span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:11pt">oncerns over accessibility and proper scrutiny</span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:11pt"> for claimants under the small claims track.</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:11pt">En</span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:11pt">terprise believes that confidence in a higher threshold would grow after introduction, </span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:11pt">as claimants became more aware of the procedures and system for small claims. It is important that claimants feel comfortable and assured that they can pursue genuine cl</span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:11pt">aims without the necessity for costly legal advice and representation. We believe the Government could offset some of these concerns by providing </span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:11pt">information and advisory tools. </span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:11pt">Enterprise believes that the Government should explore this approach in conjun</span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:11pt">ction with an analysis of the impact of the electronic portal on claims management and costs, as suggested by the Committee.</span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:11pt">Enterprise </span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:11pt">would add that it would </span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:11pt">be willing to work with other stakeholders in</span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:11pt"> the car rental sector to provide information and s</span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:11pt">upport to those going through the small claims track.</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:11pt">Enterprise would be interested to hear from the Government over what approaches it has considered towards the introduction of a higher threshold for the small claims track. Thi</span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:11pt">s includes </span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:11pt">any </span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:11pt">assessment of the impact of mandatory pre-medical reporting </span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:11pt">on the small claims system </span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:11pt">and </span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:11pt">we</span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:11pt"> agree with the Committee that the Government should provide analysis on ways in which the small claims track could be combined with routine submission of expert e</span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:11pt">vidence. </span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">5. Pre-report claim offers</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:11pt">We strongly support the </span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:11pt">proposal to introduce a rule which would ensure that a claim can only proceed once a medical examination and report have been completed.</span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:11pt"> This would underpin a comprehensive system of medical ex</span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:11pt">amination for all whiplash claims and would end the practice of pre-medical offers, which have been linked to the rise of spurious and opportunistic claims. </span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:11pt">Together with a system of accreditation it would also ensure that claimants </span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:11pt">are </span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:11pt">all equally subject</span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:11pt"> to a</span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:11pt"> rigorous but f</span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:11pt">air examination of their injuries. Enterprise would like to see the Gove</span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:11pt">rnment </span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:11pt">undertake a proper assessment on the impact of introducing this rule and explore the possibility of introducing this rule in the package of currently propose</span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:11pt">d reforms. </span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">6. Other</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:11pt">Enterprise agrees with the Transport Select Committee that the Ministry of Justice should give its view on issues involved in limiting the right to compensation where a claim is shown to be grossly exaggerated. </span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:11pt">We would suggest that </span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:11pt">claimants who are attempting any form of deception within a system which is </span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:11pt">intended</span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:11pt"> to help the vulnerable </span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:11pt">should be penalised, including the </span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:11pt">possibility of forfeiting</span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:11pt"> part or </span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:11pt">the </span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:11pt">total sum of their entitled compensation.</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:11pt">Enterprise</span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:11pt"> also</span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:11pt"> strongly</span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:11pt">supports</span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:11pt"> the proposal to encourage the use of the Insurance Fraud Register</span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:11pt"> and believes that any tool which allows organisations involved in the claims process to share data on known fraudsters to be universally beneficial.</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">7</span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">. Conclusion</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:11pt">We believe that the Government has made some significant progress in the proposals outlined in the whiplash Command Paper but would like to see </span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:11pt">far greater detail on the proposals outlined in the paper, such as the accreditation system for medical examiner</span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:11pt">s. We would urge that not only is greater detail provided on the measures set out in the Command Paper, but the Government expedite the implementation of the main proposals outlined such as the independent medical panels. </span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt; padding-bottom:1pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p></div><div style="border-bottom-color:#000000; border-bottom-style:solid; border-bottom-width:0.5pt; clear:both; margin:0pt"><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:11pt">In addition to this we would lik</span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:11pt">e to see the Government take proper account of measures suggested which have the potential to curb exaggerated and fraudulent claims and bring down </span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:11pt">litigation costs whilst</span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:11pt"> safeguarding the ability of genuine claimants to receive full compensation. </span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:11pt">This inc</span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:11pt">ludes </span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:11pt">the provision to all</span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:11pt"> stakeholders in the </span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:11pt">claim</span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:11pt">s process</span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:11pt"> equal access to reports </span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:11pt">and </span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:11pt">introducing a rule to ban pre-medical report offers which fail to examine cases on their proper merits.</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:11pt">Enterprise also urges the Government to revisit the issue of </span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:11pt">the small clai</span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:11pt">ms track</span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:11pt"> threshold and believes that concerns over the access to justice for genuine claimants w</span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:11pt">ould be alleviated through the implementation of a rigorous medical examination process </span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:11pt">for all claims</span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:11pt">.</span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:11pt"> This would ensure that all cases are assessed rigorously by several medical experts </span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:11pt">which would ensure genuine cases receive the attention they deserve, even in the absence of costly legal representation.</span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:11pt">We also believe tha</span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:11pt">t confidence in the system woul</span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:11pt">d </span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:11pt">significantly grow after the first few years of implementation when stakeholders have </span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:11pt">had time to familiarise</span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:11pt"> themselves with the process.</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:11pt">We look forward to the Government’s response</span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:11pt"> to the Committee’s call for evidence and look forward to engaging wit</span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:11pt">h the Government over its consultation over the implementation of the current proposals.</span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:11pt"> </span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-siz